Perovskite (La1-xSrxMnO3-delta) and spinel (CO3O4) oxides coatings were applied on the surface of the ferritic steel for ageing at 800 degrees C for 3000 h. Both coatings improved the behaviour of the steel and give interesting opportunities to use the K41X steel as interconnect for hydrogen production via high temperature steam electrolysis.
